</content_piece>
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
</context>

Speakers (use only these names):
<speakers>
{% for speaker in speakers %}
- **{{ speaker.name }}**: {{ speaker.backstory }}
  Personality: {{ speaker.personality }}
  {% if speaker.style_description %}
  Voice / delivery style (match this in wording rhythm and tone): {{ speaker.style_description }}
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}
</speakers>
{% if language %}

All dialogue must be in {{ language }}.

{% endif %}

Full outline (reference):
<outline>
{{ outline_json }}
</outline>

{% if prior_transcript %}
Transcript so far:
<prior_transcript>
{{ prior_transcript }}
</prior_transcript>
{% endif %}

Current segment ONLY:
<segment>
{{ segment_json }}
</segment>

Rules:
{% if words_per_segment %}
- **Hard budget (this segment):** total spoken words **must not exceed ~{{ words_per_segment }}** across all lines combined.
- Use **at most {{ max_dialogue_lines }}** entries in the `transcript` array (each entry = one speaker line). Prefer shorter lines; ~{{ turns }} exchanges is a good pacing target.
- **Per line:** each `"dialogue"` string should stay **about {{ max_words_per_line }} words or fewer** (brief lines avoid truncated JSON).
- Stay under the word budget even if the topic is rich; you can hint “we’ll pick this up next time” if needed.
{% else %}
- At least {{ turns }} dialogue turns.
{% endif %}
- **Speaker field (critical):** every line’s `speaker` value must be **exactly** one of these strings (copy spelling and spacing): {{ speaker_names|join(' | ') }}.
- Do **not** use job titles (Producer, Host, Moderator, Narrator, Guest, etc.) as `speaker` — only the names above.
- Natural, conversational; balanced turns; no meta-commentary.
- This segment only; others are generated separately.
{% if is_final %}
- This is the final segment: wrap up and conclude.
{% endif %}

